{"lemma":"سَلْبِ","slug":"سَلْبِ","root":"س.ل.ب","root_slug":"س-ل-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ل-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":6,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":9},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n20326","n20327","n20328","n20329"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%92%D8%A8%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to rape, to seize to take away, to rob, to snatch, to grab, to strip"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to deprive of, to keep back, to withhold","tags":["ditransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to dress in mourning clothes"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to put mourning clothes onto"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of سَلَبَ (salaba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"negation","tags":["negative"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of سَلِبَ (saliba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"spoil, booty, loot"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of سِلاب (silāb, “mourning gown”)","tags":["form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n20326","headword_ar":"سِلْبٌ","root":"slb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"longest"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the apparatus of the plough:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, M, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a piece of wood that is joined to the base of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"luw^omap","text_ar":"لُوْمَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[here meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ploughshare"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its end being"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inserted"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the hole,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perforation, of the latter."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.)"}],"source_refs":["AHn","M","K"]},{"entry_id":"n20327","headword_ar":"سَلَبٌ","root":"slb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saliybN","text_ar":"سَلِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Spoil, plunder,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"booty;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is seized,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"carried off, by force,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Msb, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from a man, of spoils, whatever it be;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"comprising all the clothing that is upon the man;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb, TA;) accord. to Lth and Az (Mgh) and the Bári'; (Msb;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whatever one of two antagonists in war takes from the other, of the things upon him and with him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of clothes and weapons, and his beast:"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEalN","text_ar":"فَعَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafoEuwlN","text_ar":"مَفْعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e., (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masoluwbN","text_ar":"مَسْلُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[used in the manner of a subst., or as an epithet in which the quality of a subst. is predominant]: (Mgh, TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asolaAbN","text_ar":"اَسْلَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, A, Msb, K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axa*a","text_ar":"اَخَذَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salaba Alqatiyli","text_ar":"سَلَبَ القَتِيلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He took the spoil of the slain man"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asolaAba AlqatolaY","text_ar":"اَسْلَابَ القَتْلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the spoils of the slain"},{"kind":"text","text":"men]. (A.) ―         -b3-  Also (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hide and shanks and paunch"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a slaughtered animal. (K. [App. so called because given to the slaughterer, as though they were his spoil; or, in the case of an animal of the chase, to the dog or dogs: see the verses cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badanN","text_ar":"بَدَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b4-  And (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"peel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"skin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of a cane, or reed, (K, TA,) and of a tree. (TA.) And [particularly] The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bark,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rind, of a kind of tree"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in El-Yemen, of which ropes are made,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and which is coarser and harder than the fibres of the Theban palm-tree:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) hence it is that a well-known kind of [thick] rope [made of the fibres of the common palm-tree] is called by the vulgar ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salabapN","text_ar":"سَلَبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bark of a kind of tree of which are made"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"baskets of the kind called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"silaAl","text_ar":"سِلَال"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Sh, TA:) there is a market called ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suwqu Als~al~aAbiyna","text_ar":"سُوقُ السَّلَّابِينَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"in El-Medeeneh, (Sh, S, K, TA,) and in Mekkeh also, as being the market [of the sellers, or manufacturers, of what are made] of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salab","text_ar":"سَلَب"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Sh, TA:) it is also [said to be] (K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain kind of tall tree,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"growing symmetrically, which is taken and laid beneath hot ashes"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yumal~u","text_ar":"يُمَلُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and then split asunder, whereupon there comes forth form it a white"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mu$aAqap","text_ar":"مُشَاقَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coarse fibrous substance"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the fibres of the palm-tree, called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liyf","text_ar":"لِيف"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it is one of the best of the materials of which ropes are made:"},{"kind":"text","text":"the n. un. is with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) and (M, K) AHn says, (M,) it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain plant"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which grows in form like candles, except that it is larger and longer, and of which are made ropes of every sort:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) and (M, K) some say, (M,) it is the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fibrous substance"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lyf","text_ar":"ليف"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the Theban palm-tree,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,) this Lth asserts it to be, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is brought from Mekkeh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,) and Lth adds,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and it is white;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but Az says that Lth has erred respecting it: A'Obeyd says, I asked respecting it, and was told, it is not the fibrous substance of the Theban palm-tree, but is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind of tree well known in El-Yemen, of which ropes are made:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and some say that it is the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuwS","text_ar":"خُوص"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leaves"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vamaAm","text_ar":"ثَمَام"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"panic grass"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and this [says SM] is what is commonly known among us in El-Yemen: (TA:) [accord. to Forskål, (Flor. Aegypt. Arab., p. cx.) this name is applied in El-Yemen to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a species of hyacinth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"which he terms"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hyacinthus aporus."},{"kind":"text","text":"] A poet says, (S,) namely, [Murrah] Ibn-Mahkán [El-Temeemee], (M,)"},{"kind":"quote","text":"fana$ona$a Aljiloda EanohaAwahoYa baArikapN\n                      \n                     \n                        kamaA tuna$oni$u kaf~aA faAtilK salabaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, *) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And he stripped off quickly the skin"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from her, while she was lying upon her breast, like as the two hands of the twister"},{"kind":"text","text":"of ropes"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strips off quickly the seleb"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n$","text_ar":"نش"},{"kind":"text","text":":) some read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAtilK","text_ar":"قَاتِلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning [by the word following it] “ what is seized, or carried off by force, from one slain: ” (M:) As read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAtilK","text_ar":"فَاتِلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"f","text_ar":"ف"},{"kind":"text","text":"; IAar, with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"q","text_ar":"ق"},{"kind":"text","text":": Th says that the right reading is that of As. (S in the present art.)"}],"source_refs":["M","Msb","K","TA","Mgh","S","Sh"]},{"entry_id":"n20328","headword_ar":"سَلِبٌ","root":"slb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Light,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"active,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and quick."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN salibu Alyadayoni biAlT~aEoni","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ سَلِبُ اليَدَيْنِ بِالطَّعْنِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man light,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"active, in the arms,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hands, in thrusting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piercing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vaworN salibu AlT~aEoni biAlqaroni","text_ar":"ثَوْرٌ سَلِبُ الطَّعْنِ بِالقَرْنِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A bull light,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"active, in thrusting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piercing, with the horn."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farasN salibu AlqawaAy^imi","text_ar":"فَرَسٌ سَلِبُ القَوَايِمِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A horse light,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"active,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the legs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,) [i. e.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the shifting of the legs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or, accord. to Az, the right meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"long in the legs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [for] ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salibN","text_ar":"سَلِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Long"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tall;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K;) applied to a spear, and to a man [&c.]: pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sulubN","text_ar":"سُلُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","S","M"]},{"entry_id":"n20329","headword_ar":"سُلُبٌ","root":"slb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", as a sing., see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saliybN","text_ar":"سَلِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places. ―         -b2-  It is also a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salibN","text_ar":"سَلِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v., last sentence]: (M:) and of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"silaAbN","text_ar":"سِلَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as a subst.: (S, K:) and of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saluwbN","text_ar":"سَلُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as an epithet applied to a spear: (Ham p. 171:) and of the same, (S, M,) or of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"silaAbN","text_ar":"سِلَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) as an epithet applied to a she-camel (S, M) and to a woman: (M:) and of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saliybN","text_ar":"سَلِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as an epithet applied to a tree. (S.)"}],"source_refs":["M","S","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}